<br>
Banarus: In all likelihood, no-one here can answer that question definitively and objectively.  It's almost a religious debate amongst enchanters.  Some favor INT, some favor HP/AC, some favor CHA.  Personally, I started off focusing on my CHA gear because it's the hardest to get.  At 200+ CHA, I'm now working on my INT gear.  After that, I plan to start working on HP/AC gear.<br>
<br>
The truth of the matter is, at your level HP/AC gear isn't going to be that important.  It took me a long time to learn this, but we aren't made of glass.  When you get to higher levels, you're going to have to worry alot more about getting hit.  INT gear is a different question.  One I can't give you an answer to.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to jump on anyone here, but if you ask 20 enchanters which path they'd take - INT, CHA, or HP/AC - you'll get 20 different answers.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It's pretty much a choice you have to make for yourself.  I'd love to give you enough information to make that choice, but I haven't the experience to do so myself, and the task of compiling an objective view of the advantages to each path is daunting to say the least.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><center><img src=http://home.netcom.com/~awachs/Sig9-37.JPG> <BR>
